      "content": "but \"small actions\" feel like a joke. like, what does it matter if i recycle or buy local if the whole system is just fundamentally broken? it feels like people are just pretending everything is fine so they don't have to face the truth. it's exhausting to keep pretending there's a point to any of this. like, why even bother building a life or making plans when the foundation is just rotting away?",
